          node and edge nodes. Web sockets for remote communication were used in order to handle constraints imposed by client firewalls and to allow real-time control.
          Remote functions were defined explicitly in order to pass audits. Central node also acted as a monitoring system for edge nodes.
          Supported relay nodes between central and edge nodes in order to accommodate network segmentation by clients.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <span class="text-xs bg-primary/20 text-primary px-2 py-1 rounded">Golang</span>
          <span class="text-xs bg-primary/20 text-primary px-2 py-1 rounded">Web Sockets</span>
          <span class="text-xs bg-primary/20 text-primary px-2 py-1 rounded">Gitlab CI</span>
          <span class="text-xs bg-primary/20 text-primary px-2 py-1 rounded">On-Premise</span>
          <span class="text-xs bg-primary/20 text-primary px-2 py-1 rounded">Amazon Web Services</span>
          <span class="text-xs bg-primary/20 text-primary px-2 py-1 rounded">Hashicorp Terraform</span>
          <span class="text-xs bg-primary/20 text-primary px-2 py-1 rounded">Agile Development</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Robi Backend -->
      <div class="bg-surface-light rounded-xl p-8 border border-white/10">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Robi Backend (now robi T)</h3>
          <div class="flex gap-3 text-sm text-text-muted">
